{# Two-card callout at the top of `/app/mailboxes` (the "Report ingestion"
   page). Encodes Sendvery's product preference for DNS-based ingestion: the
   left card is the recommended path (publish RUA pointing at our central
   inbox), the right card is the fallback (connect your own mailbox) for
   customers who can't change DNS.

   The literal substring "Connect a mailbox" appears ONLY inside the
   `data-testid="fallback-callout"` element — guarded by a regression test
   so future refactors can't accidentally re-introduce unqualified
   mailbox-first copy elsewhere on the page.

   TASK-105: when `allScenarioB` is true (every domain in the matrix below
   already routes DMARC reports to Sendvery), the two-card layout collapses
   to a single confirmation card — the fallback CTA is noise the matrix
   contradicts row-by-row. The recommended/fallback split returns the
   moment ANY domain is on a different scenario (mixed team, scenario c,
   no record yet) so the educational copy keeps showing for users who
   haven't decided yet.

   Props:
     - reportAddress (string)  e.g. "reports@sendvery.com"; the address the
                               team's DMARC RUA tag should point at.
     - dnsCtaUrl (string)      Pre-resolved URL for the "View DMARC setup"
                               CTA — single-domain teams land on the per-domain
                               health page, multi-domain teams on the DNS Health
                               overview.
     - allScenarioB (bool)     Pre-computed by the controller (true when the
                               whole matrix is scenario PointsAtSendvery).
                               Defaults to false so any caller that hasn't
                               opted in still gets the original two-card
                               layout.
#}
{% props reportAddress, dnsCtaUrl, allScenarioB = false %}

{% if allScenarioB %}
    {# COLLAPSED — every domain already routes via Sendvery. One quiet
       confirmation card replaces the two-card educational split. The
       fallback link remains accessible for the genuinely-edge-case operator
       who still wants to add a private mailbox, but it's a `link link-hover`
       instead of a button so it doesn't compete with the affirmation. #}
    <div data-testid="all-scenario-b-callout"
         class="card border border-success/30 bg-success/5 shadow-sm mb-6">
        <div class="card-body p-5">
            <h3 class="font-bold text-base sm:text-lg leading-snug">
                Every domain is ingesting reports via Sendvery's central inbox
            </h3>
            <p class="text-sm text-base-content/70 mt-2 leading-relaxed">
                Nothing to set up here — your DMARC <code class="kbd kbd-xs">rua=</code> tags already point at
                <code class="kbd kbd-xs">{{ reportAddress }}</code> for every monitored domain.
            </p>
            <div class="mt-3">
                <a href="{{ path('dashboard_mailbox_add') }}"
                   class="link link-hover text-sm text-base-content/60">
                    Connect a private mailbox anyway →
                </a>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
{% else %}
    <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-4 mb-6">
        {# RECOMMENDED — DNS-based ingestion #}
        <div data-testid="recommended-callout"
             class="card border border-primary/30 bg-primary/5 shadow-sm">
            <div class="card-body p-5">
                <span class="badge badge-primary badge-sm font-semibold mb-2 w-fit">Recommended</span>
                <h3 class="font-bold text-base sm:text-lg leading-snug">DNS-based ingestion</h3>
                <p class="text-sm text-base-content/70 mt-2 leading-relaxed">
                    Publish <code class="kbd kbd-xs">rua=mailto:{{ reportAddress }}</code> in your domain's DMARC TXT
                    record. Email providers (Gmail, Outlook, Yahoo) deliver reports to Sendvery's central inbox — nothing
                    to configure here.
                </p>
                <div class="card-actions mt-4">
                    <a href="{{ dnsCtaUrl }}" class="btn btn-primary btn-sm">
                        View DMARC setup →
                    </a>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>

        {# FALLBACK — Connect a mailbox. The only place on this page allowed to
           say "Connect a mailbox" — locked by the regression test. #}
        <div data-testid="fallback-callout"
             class="card border border-base-200 bg-base-100 shadow-sm">
            <div class="card-body p-5">
                <h3 class="font-bold text-base sm:text-lg leading-snug">Connect a mailbox (fallback)</h3>
                <p class="text-sm text-base-content/70 mt-2 leading-relaxed">
                    Already receiving DMARC reports at a private inbox — e.g. you can't change DNS, or you want a local
                    copy? Connect that mailbox <strong>if you can't change DNS</strong> and Sendvery polls it every
                    5 minutes.
                </p>
                <div class="card-actions mt-4">
                    <a href="{{ path('dashboard_mailbox_add') }}" class="btn btn-ghost btn-sm">
                        Connect a mailbox
                    </a>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
{% endif %}
